abstract: Three months after Bloomberg News tried to thread the needle with a plan for covering a presidential campaign with company founder Mike Bloomberg as a candidate, its journalists are learning how hard that can be.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Three months after Bloomberg News tried to thread the needle with a plan for covering a presidential campaign with company founder Mike Bloomberg as a candidate, its journalists are learning how hard that can be.

abstract: President Donald Trump's new acting director of national intelligence is facing criticism that he doesn't have the right experience for the job. Richard Grenell is the American ambassador to Germany and he's served as a spokesman in various roles in government. But he has little background in intelligence or in running the sprawling bureaucracy of the nation's 17 spy agencies.

abstract: Bernie Sanders will have to win over voters whose skepticism of socialism has been shaped by Latin American authoritarian leaders.
snippet: Bernie Sanders will have to win over voters whose skepticism of socialism has been shaped by Latin American authoritarian leaders.
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders’s message has resonated with the Latino electorate, particularly young voters. In both Iowa and New Hampshire, he won big among Latinos, and he is projected to do the same in Nevada this Saturday. But whether that support will transfer to a general election if “Tío Bernie” (Uncle Bernie), as he is known, manages to clinch the nomination is the big question.

abstract: Morgan Stanley's takeover of brokerage E*Trade Financial Corp  reflects a more relaxed regulatory mood in Washington, but it is still a gamble in an election year that will see Democrats continue to shine a spotlight on Wall Street excesses, said analysts.
snippet: Morgan Stanley's takeover of brokerage E*Trade Financial Corp  reflects a more relaxed regulatory mood in Washington, but it is still a gamble in an election year that will see Democrats continue to shine a spotlight on Wall Street excesses, said ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Morgan Stanley's takeover of brokerage E*Trade Financial Corp  reflects a more relaxed regulatory mood in Washington, but it is still a gamble in an election year that will see Democrats continue to shine a spotlight on Wall Street excesses, said analysts.
headline_main: Morgan Stanley's E*Trade Deal to Test Washington's Regulatory Mood in Election Year
headline_print_headline: Morgan Stanley's E*Trade Deal to Test Washington's Regulatory Mood in Election Year

abstract: Roger J. Stone Jr., the Republican political consultant and friend of President Trump, was sentenced to more than three years in prison for obstructing a congressional inquiry.

abstract: The White House “does not put any stock” in the rumor that Victoria Coates, the aide, wrote an Op-Ed essay in The Times in 2018, an administration official said.
snippet: The White House “does not put any stock” in the rumor that Victoria Coates, the aide, wrote an Op-Ed essay in The Times in 2018, an administration official said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House is transferring a senior national security aide who fell under suspicion of writing an anonymous insider account of dissent within the Trump administration, the latest of several senior personnel moves stemming from questions of loyalty to President Trump.

abstract: Ukraine is happy that impeachment proceedings against President Donald Trump, which the country got dragged into, are over and it now wants to “advance" relations with the United States, Ukraine's foreign minister said Thursday.
snippet: Ukraine is happy that impeachment proceedings against President Donald Trump, which the country got dragged into, are over and it now wants to “advance" relations with the United States, Ukraine's foreign minister said Thursday.
lead_paragraph: UNITED NATIONS — Ukraine is happy that impeachment proceedings against President Donald Trump, which the country got dragged into, are over and it now wants to “advance" relations with the United States, Ukraine's foreign minister said Thursday.
headline_main: Ukraine Happy Impeachment Is Over, Wants to Advance US Ties
headline_print_headline: Ukraine Happy Impeachment Is Over, Wants to Advance US Ties

abstract: With a clear voice and a bit of suspense, Karen Blumenthal’s “Jane Against the World” charts the rocky road that led to legal abortion in the United States.
